<p>Welcome to the fifth episode of 15 Minutes In Hell.</p><p>Today&#8217;s guest is <a href="https://www.1thousandmonkeys.com/">TV writer David Slack</a> (credits include Person of Interest, Teen Titans, Law &amp; Order, Lie To Me, Jackie Chan Adventures, and Dark Crystal), who was also on the Writer&#8217;s Guild of America West&#8217;s Board from 2018 to 2022. </p><p>I had David on to cut through the noise around the TV strike - what&#8217;s happening, why it&#8217;s happening, what the stakes are, and why Hollywood executives are fighting a losing battle against some of the strongest unions in the world.</p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ylitz-NmRno">The 15 Minutes In Hell Theme</a> is written and performed by <a href="https://www.patreon.com/Eve6ix">Eve6</a>.</p><p>If you&#8217;ve enjoyed <a href="http://wheresyoured.at/podcast">this podcast</a>, subscribe free to Ed&#8217;s newsletter <a href="http://wheresyoured.at">Where&#8217;s Your Heart Ed At</a>, or join us at the <a href="http://chat.wheresyoured.at">Where&#8217;s Your Ed At Discord</a>.</p>